MOST IMMEDIATE
No.1/34/1/2013-Cab.
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA (BHARAT SARKAR)
CABINET SECRETARIAT (MANTRIMANDAL SACHIVALAYA)
New Delhi, the 11th May, 2013
The undersigned is directed to say that with effect from the 11th May, 2013:
(i)
Shri Ashwani Kumar relinquished the charge of the offic
he Minister of Law and
Justice;
(ii)
Shri Pawan Kumar Bansal relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of
Railways;
(iii) Shri Kapil Sibal assumed the additional charge of the office of the Minister of Law and
Justice. He will continue to hold the charge of the office of the Minister of
Communications and Information Technology; and
(iv) Shri C.P. Joshi assumed the additional charge of the office of the Minister of Railways.
He will continue to hold the charge of the office of the Minister of Road Transport and
Highways.
(K.L. Sharma)
for Cabinet Secretary
Tele : 2301 5802
To
All Members of the Council of Ministers.
Copy forwarded for information to the Deputy Chairman and Members of the Planning.
Commission.
(K.L. Sharma)
for Cabinet Secretary
Copy forwarded for information to:
Secretary to the President.
Secretary to the Vice-President.
(K.L. Sharma)
Joint Secretary (Cabinet)
Copy also forwarded for information to:
Principal Secretary to the Prime Minister.
(K.L. Sharma)
